  • Class
    Description
    AddMoodEventActivity
    This activity allows the user to select a mood, specify a trigger, and choose a social situation which is then saved to Firestore.
    AdminActivity
    This activity provides the interface for admin users, implements UI experience and adjusts the layout to account for system insets (such as the status bar and navigation bar) to allows admin users
    AdminLoginFrag
    This fragment for admin login that allows navigation back to the user selection screen and provides a UI for admin users to sign in and access the admin panel.
    CommunityFrag
    This fragment provides a user interface for the community area where users can interact with each other and displays content related to community interactions and discussions for the community section of the app.
    EditDeleteMoodActivity
    This fragment allows the user to edit and delete a mood event by providing a user interface for modifying stored mood data including interactive buttons like save, delete and back (to navigate back to MainActivity).
    FollowerRequestFrag
    This fragment displays and manages incoming and outgoing follow requests and provides a UI layout where users can review follow request.
    HomeMapFrag
    Fragment that displays a map for mood-related locations.
    HomeMyMoodsFilterFrag
    Fragment that provides filtering options for mood events.
    HomeMyMoodsFrag
    A fragment that displays the logged-in user's mood events.

    Manages user login and stores the logged-in username.
    LoginUserSelectionFrag
    Fragment for selecting user or admin login.
    MainActivity
    This activity allows the user to navigate between pages from the home page.
